// THIS DOCUMENT IS FOR THE USE OF CSCOPE FOR EXAMINIG A C SOURCE_FILE

--> First you need to install the toolkit of cscope by using "sudo apt install cscope"

--> Go to the working directory and open terminal

--> Now run "$cscope -R"  you will enter the menu of the cscope

--> Use them accordingly

--> TO exit the cscope menu use "Ctrl+D";

--> Any changes made from the Cscope menu shall be reflected only after executing the "Ctrl+D"


--> For grep you can give any source of string for Example the string is "Happy Days" we can give a search pattern to the grep by using H*.s as the pattern.

--> Now next step.




